                <note rend="inline" type="source">751G.94/401</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by the Assistant Chief of the
                        Division of Far Eastern Affairs</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>)<note
                        n="39" xml:id="d371fn1">Initialed by the Chief of the Division
                        (Hamilton).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-11-22">November 22,
                            1941</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Hayter of the British Embassy informed Mr. Smyth during a call on November
                    22, 1941 that according to a recent telegram from the British Minister at
                    Bangkok, Japanese members of the Thai-Indochina Boundary Commission are asking
                    for the use of some Thai airdromes for “survey flights” and also for aviation
                    gasoline from Thailand, presumably to be used in these flights. Mr. Hayter added
                    that this information had been given to the British at Bangkok by the Thai
                    Minister of Foreign Affairs.</p>
            </div>
